article.headline: Phoenix rise behind Loiselle's 20 points
article.story:
DETROIT (AP) -- Kristy Loiselle scored 20 points as Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) beat Detroit 76-52 on Saturday.

	   Elizabeth Dudley added 14 points for the Phoenix (19-3, 10-1
Horizon League). Wisconsin-Green Bay finished 12-for-24 from behind
the arc. Loiselle was 8-for-11 and had a game-high six assists and
five steals.

	   Caitie Goddard made all three of her 3-point attempts and led
the Titans (7-14, 5-5) with 17 points. Nicole Anaejionu added 14
points and a game-high nine rebounds.

	   The Phoenix, who beat Detroit 86-53 on Jan. 4 in Green Bay, led
31-24 at halftime and stretched their lead in the second half by
shooting 55 percent from the field while holding the Titans to 31
percent.

	   Detroit went to the free-throw line only five times, making
three.
